<subSubSection id="AEDFF44956A8F153F97CDA96061BF943" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6144B08C461279C77F213021ADE02F60">
Voisine de 
<taxonomicName id="71069DBDC6E02561B2A55667C3E535E6" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33342" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pachycondyla" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachycondyla pachyderma Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pachycondyla pachyderma Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachyderma">pachyderma</taxonomicName>
et de 
<taxonomicName id="F539AAE61327329986D2D4B5578A7701" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33409" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pachycondyla" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachycondyla wasmannii (Forel)" lsidName-HNS="Pachycondyla wasmannii (Forel)" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasmannii">wasmani</taxonomicName>
, mais les cotes de la tete sont plus convexes, les scapes plus longs chez cette derniere.
</paragraph>
